==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filipendulous
<hw>Fil`i*pen"du*lous</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>filum</ets> a thread + <ets>pendulus</ets> hanging, fr.
<ets>pend⟦emac⟧re</ets> to hang.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Suspended
by, or strung upon, a thread; -- said of tuberous swellings in the
middle or at the extremities of slender, threadlike rootlets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filipino</ent>⟦br⟧
